    <remark>
      <title>The <m>\frac{1}{3}</m> Pattern</title>
      <p>We will see that pointed shapes (pyramids, cones) always have exactly <m>\frac{1}{3}</m> the volume of their flat-topped counterparts (prisms, cylinders) with the same base and height. This is a recurring theme throughout the chapter.</p>
    </remark>
  </subsection>

